7:
Another day gone, and no sign of
Grey.
11: Geez... Where could that old man be?
13:
A good retainer doesn't just
disappear without a word!
16:
This is the first time he's left me
alone for so long...
21:
Am I supposed to sit here and do
nothing?
27:
So about the job, we're supposed to
look into the monsters coming out
of this unexplored forest, right?
31:
Correct. Apparently, even the
bravest hunters stay clear of these
woods.
35:
I don't blame them. Something is off
about all this.
39:
The town and the castle look
beautiful though.
43:
Beautiful it may be, but Alk is right.
Why would anyone want to build a
settlement in the middle of nowhere?
46:
The trees practically brush up
against the buildings, and there
aren't even any people around—
51:
Wait, no... Someone's being attacked
over there!
58:
Can't you flee any faster? They have
guns, and they do not seem keen on
chatting!
61:
It's too late. They've already caught
up to us...
67:
V-very well, I shall demonstrate my
aptitude for defense! This will be a
simple matter!
70:
Come at me, one at a time, and turn
your aim away from any of my
handsome features!
80:
Alk?! Stella! Light! What in the world
are the lot of you doing here?
83:
Never mind, don't answer that! I
need help protecting this little runt!
Please say you'll lend a hand!
87:
How do you always say lame stuff
like that with a straight face...
92:
Enough banter! We have incoming
foes!
